hall be able to have a rest. Yesterday I went to see the doctor, who found me overworked. I really want to see you.

Yours,

V. Nabokov2





TO: KENNETH D. MCCORMICK1

CC, 1 p.

Cambridge, Mass.





22nd September 1946

Dear Mr. McCormick,

I am writing you to explain a few things about my next book.2 This will be a new kind of autobiography, or rather a new hybrid between that and a novel. To the latter it will be affiliated by having a definite plot. Various strata of personal past will form